00:50:06,127 --> 00:50:09,289
Correct. That just what he is too.
He's a circus mouse.

509
00:50:09,496 --> 00:50:11,521
When I get out,
he'll make me rich.

510
00:50:11,932 --> 00:50:14,264
You just watch and see
if he don't do that.

511
00:50:14,568 --> 00:50:16,763
Play fetch? We play fetch again?

512
00:50:17,404 --> 00:50:19,235
Well, well, well.

513
00:50:19,707 --> 00:50:21,902
Looks like you found yourself
a new friend.

514
00:50:22,576 --> 00:50:23,941
Don't hurt him.

515
00:50:25,479 --> 00:50:27,913
- Okay?
- Is that the one I chased?

516
00:50:28,315 --> 00:50:29,976
Yeah, that's the one.

517
00:50:30,484 --> 00:50:33,749
Only Del says his name is Mr. Jingles.

518
00:50:34,822 --> 00:50:35,880
Is that so?

519
00:50:37,091 --> 00:50:38,786
Del's been asking for a box.

520
00:50:39,593 --> 00:50:43,393
Thinks the mouse will sleep in it,
I guess. Might keep it for a pet.

521
00:50:45,766 --> 00:50:47,063
What do you think?

522
00:50:48,302 --> 00:50:52,135
You know what?
We ought to find a cigar box...

523
00:50:52,605 --> 00:50:57,235
...and get some cotton batting
from the dispensary to line it with.

524
00:50:59,545 --> 00:51:02,605
Yeah. That should do real nice.

525
00:51:11,991 --> 00:51:14,459
Man said get a cigar box.

526
00:51:24,070 --> 00:51:25,537
Morning.

527
00:51:30,376 --> 00:51:32,401
Hal, you wanted to see me?

528
00:51:32,679 --> 00:51:33,976
Yeah.

529
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:36,038
Close the door.

530
00:51:43,322 --> 00:51:45,051
So you know...

531
00:51:46,558 --> 00:51:49,049
...you got a new prisoner
coming in here tomorrow.

532
00:51:50,162 --> 00:51:51,823
"William Wharton."

533
00:51:52,564 --> 00:51:54,225
He's what you call...

534
00:51:54,533 --> 00:51:56,501
...a problem child.

535
00:51:57,369 --> 00:52:01,066
Got "Billy the Kid" tattooed
on his left arm.

536
00:52:01,273 --> 00:52:05,334
Been rambling all over the state
last few years...

537
00:52:05,777 --> 00:52:07,972
...causing all kinds of trouble.

538
00:52:08,747 --> 00:52:10,681
Finally hit the big time.

539
00:52:12,084 --> 00:52:15,383
Killed three people in a holdup.

540
00:52:15,587 --> 00:52:17,714
One of them a pregnant woman.

541
00:52:20,225 --> 00:52:22,215
Bad news all around.

542
00:52:24,228 --> 00:52:25,695
Hal?

543
00:52:36,640 --> 00:52:37,902
It's a tumor, Paul.

544
00:52:39,577 --> 00:52:41,306
A brain tumor.

545
00:52:43,047 --> 00:52:44,708
They got...

546
00:52:45,049 --> 00:52:47,142
...x- ray pictures of it.

547
00:52:48,552 --> 00:52:51,077
It's the size of a lemon, they said.

548
00:52:53,791 --> 00:52:55,053
And...

549
00:52:56,227 --> 00:52:57,751
...way down...

550
00:52:59,597 --> 00:53:01,792
...deep inside,
where they can't operate.

551
00:53:03,834 --> 00:53:05,495
I haven't told her.

552
00:53:07,270 --> 00:53:09,238
I can't think how.

553
00:53:13,009 --> 00:53:15,136
For the life of me, Paul...

554
00:53:16,646 --> 00:53:19,638
...I can't think how
to tell my wife...

555
00:53:23,119 --> 00:53:25,087
...she's going to die.

556
00:54:50,204 --> 00:54:51,831
Oh, God.

557
00:54:52,507 --> 00:54:54,065
Oh, God.

558
00:54:57,945 --> 00:54:59,344
I'm going.

559
00:54:59,547 --> 00:55:03,540
- What?
- To see Dr. Bishop. I'm going.

560
00:55:03,885 --> 00:55:05,352
Today.

561
00:55:05,853 --> 00:55:08,788
Soon as we get that new inmate
squared away.

562
00:55:08,956 --> 00:55:10,446
That bad?

563
00:55:10,858 --> 00:55:12,291
Oh, yeah.

564
00:55:34,381 --> 00:55:36,576
The boy is doped to the gills.

565
00:55:39,553 --> 00:55:40,781
Hand me them clothes.

566
00:55:43,823 --> 00:55:45,723
William Wharton?

567
00:55:46,159 --> 00:55:49,356
Hey! You put on these clothes now,
you hear?

568
00:55:57,470 --> 00:55:59,563
We're gonna have to do this.

569
00:56:00,807 --> 00:56:02,434
Hellraiser, huh?

570
00:56:02,642 --> 00:56:05,167
Look more like a limp noodle to me.

571
00:56:05,345 --> 00:56:08,438
Hey. Hey.

572
00:56:09,081 --> 00:56:12,881
You've been declared competent, son.
You know what that means?

573
00:56:13,619 --> 00:56:16,315
Means you're gonna ride the lightning.
Yeah.

574
00:56:17,356 --> 00:56:20,052
Percy, could you shut up,
give us a hand here?

575
00:56:20,926 --> 00:56:22,621
Hellraiser.

576
00:56:53,591 --> 00:56:55,081
You don't look so good.

577
00:56:57,061 --> 00:56:59,029
Look like you're running you a fever.

578
00:57:04,802 --> 00:57:06,394
Boss Edgecomb?

579
00:57:07,905 --> 00:57:09,839
I needs to see you down here, boss.

580
00:57:12,410 --> 00:57:15,902
I got things to tend to just now,
John Coffey. You just...

581
00:57:17,382 --> 00:57:20,749
You just stay still in your cell.

582
00:57:32,330 --> 00:57:33,558
E Block.

583
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:11,290
Come on, let's go.

584
00:58:12,536 --> 00:58:14,629
Come on. Look alive, big boy.

585
00:58:29,318 --> 00:58:30,546
Careful.

586
00:58:34,056 --> 00:58:37,219
- Careful.
- Step up. Step up.

587
00:59:11,760 --> 00:59:14,058
Where you going? Where you going?

588
00:59:17,932 --> 00:59:19,263
Ain't this a party now?

589
00:59:19,567 --> 00:59:20,795
- Is it or what?
- Let him go.

590
00:59:21,002 --> 00:59:22,629
- Shoot him.
- See who you hit.

591
00:59:22,837 --> 00:59:24,771
- Shoot the son of a bitch.
- Shoot me!

592
00:59:24,939 --> 00:59:28,306
- Shoot him!
- Hit him, Percy! Goddamn it! Hit him.

593
00:59:28,510 --> 00:59:29,977
Hit me, you limp noodle.

594
00:59:30,178 --> 00:59:32,476
Hit him, Percy!
Goddamn it, hit him!

595
00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:35,649
- Come on, Percy. Hit me.
- Wharton, I'm warning you.

596
00:59:35,850 --> 00:59:38,683
- You warning me? Warn me now.
- I'm warning you!

597
00:59:38,887 --> 00:59:40,912
- You're warning me?!
- Shoot him!

598
00:59:41,122 --> 00:59:42,487
Well, come on...

599
00:59:49,063 --> 00:59:50,962
You're a big fucker.

600
00:59:51,331 --> 00:59:52,764
Where'd you come from?

601
01:00:03,377 --> 01:00:05,868
Come on, Dean.
Come on, boy, get up.

602
01:00:06,079 --> 01:00:07,637
All right. Now, just breathe.

603
01:00:08,215 --> 01:00:10,308
That's it. Just breathe.
Just breathe.

604
01:00:12,186 --> 01:00:13,915
Breathe. Breathe, boy.

605
01:00:14,154 --> 01:00:17,123
- Didn't see it coming.
- Come on, boy, breathe.

606
01:00:17,324 --> 01:00:19,349
Come on. Just breathe.

607
01:00:22,196 --> 01:00:24,323
We thought he was doped.

608
01:00:25,599 --> 01:00:28,864
Didn't we? Didn't we, all of us,
think he was doped?

609
01:00:29,069 --> 01:00:30,798
You didn't ask?

610
01:00:32,105 --> 01:00:33,970
Well, I guess that's not a mistake...

611
01:00:34,341 --> 01:00:37,571
...you'll be needing to make again
anytime soon, is it?

612
01:00:51,624 --> 01:00:55,253
You go get Dean and Harry looked at.
Make sure they're all right.

613
01:00:55,695 --> 01:00:59,222
Percy, you make the report
to the warden for me.

614
01:00:59,432 --> 01:01:01,992
Say the situation's under control.
It's not a story.

615
01:01:02,201 --> 01:01:04,863
He won't appreciate you
drawing out the suspense.

616
01:01:05,071 --> 01:01:07,301
What about you?
You're about to collapse.

617
01:01:07,540 --> 01:01:10,873
I've got the Mile
till you all come back.

618
01:01:11,644 --> 01:01:13,612
Go on, now. Go.

619
01:01:21,286 --> 01:01:24,414
Come on, boy.
Let's get you looked at.

620
01:01:50,015 --> 01:01:53,451
Boss, I needs to see you down here.

621
01:01:56,988 --> 01:02:00,219
This is not a good time, John Coffey...

622
01:02:00,425 --> 01:02:02,393
...not a good time at all.

623
01:02:02,594 --> 01:02:06,723
But I needs to see you, boss.
I needs to talk to you.

624
01:02:28,786 --> 01:02:30,083
Closer.

625
01:02:30,621 --> 01:02:32,680
Boss, you know you ain't
supposed to do that.

626
01:02:34,325 --> 01:02:36,293
Mind your business, Del.

627
01:02:45,936 --> 01:02:47,961
What do you want, John Coffey?

628
01:02:49,038 --> 01:02:50,130
Just to help it.

629
01:02:53,810 --> 01:02:55,243
Don't be afraid.

630
01:02:55,812 --> 01:02:56,836
Help!

631
01:02:57,647 --> 01:03:00,445
Help! John Coffey's
killing Boss Edgecomb!

632
01:03:00,616 --> 01:03:02,140
Help!

633
01:03:02,352 --> 01:03:05,583
- What are you doing?
- Help!

634
01:03:08,157 --> 01:03:10,022
Boss Howell! Help!

635
01:03:10,727 --> 01:03:12,456
Boss Stanton! Somebody, come!

636
01:03:12,795 --> 01:03:14,763
Help!

637
01:03:31,180 --> 01:03:33,410
Help! Boss Howell! Boss Stanton!

638
01:03:33,616 --> 01:03:36,584
Somebody, come!
John Coffey's killing Boss Edgecomb!

639
01:03:36,785 --> 01:03:39,413
Del, for chrissakes, shut up!

640
01:04:26,000 --> 01:04:28,230
What did you just do to me?

641
01:04:30,204 --> 01:04:31,899
I helped it.

642
01:04:32,973 --> 01:04:34,600
Didn't I help it?

643
01:04:35,709 --> 01:04:37,939
I just took it back, is all.

644
01:04:38,746 --> 01:04:41,214
Awful tired now, boss.

645
01:04:41,749 --> 01:04:43,444
Dog-tired.

646
01:05:07,574 --> 01:05:10,600
Boss, what that man do to you?

647
01:06:13,071 --> 01:06:15,835
Hey, honey. How you feeling?

648
01:06:17,643 --> 01:06:20,407
Oh, not too bad.

649
01:06:21,647 --> 01:06:23,410
What did the doctor say?

650
01:06:25,651 --> 01:06:27,380
Oh, you know doctors.

651
01:06:27,819 --> 01:06:29,719
Gobbledygook, mostly.

652
01:06:30,822 --> 01:06:32,187
Gobbledygook.

653
01:06:47,438 --> 01:06:49,030
Having stew tonight.

654
01:06:59,350 --> 01:07:01,045
What are you doing?

655
01:07:07,758 --> 01:07:09,623
What does it feel like?

656
01:07:10,494 --> 01:07:12,928
Well, I know what it feels like.

657
01:07:16,567 --> 01:07:18,466
It feels great.

658
01:07:52,897 --> 01:07:54,797
- Paul.
- Yeah?

659
01:07:55,232 --> 01:07:57,962
Not that I'm complaining...

660
01:07:59,103 --> 01:08:02,833
...but we haven't gone four times
in one night since we were 19.

661
01:08:03,073 --> 01:08:05,439
Yeah, we did, at your mom's.

662
01:08:06,943 --> 01:08:08,934
Wanna tell me what's going on?

663
01:08:12,749 --> 01:08:14,114
Well...

664
01:08:15,418 --> 01:08:17,409
...see, the thing is...

665
01:08:18,621 --> 01:08:22,182
...I never actually made it in
to Dr. Bishop's yesterday.

666
01:08:25,362 --> 01:08:28,160
Brutal, Paul. Listen.

667
01:08:28,365 --> 01:08:32,802
I'm thinking of taking the morning
off sick. You cover the fort for me?

668
01:08:33,870 --> 01:08:36,134
That's swell. Thanks.

669
01:08:36,339 --> 01:08:38,967
Yeah, no, I'm sure I'll feel better.

670
01:08:39,209 --> 01:08:41,837
Okay. Okay.

671
01:08:47,217 --> 01:08:49,184
You're sure you ought to do this?

672
01:08:50,786 --> 01:08:53,016
I'm not sure what I'm sure of.

673
01:09:09,838 --> 01:09:12,830
Burt, you got some company.

674
01:09:13,509 --> 01:09:15,101
Can I offer you a cold drink?

675
01:09:15,344 --> 01:09:18,438
Oh, yes, ma'am. A cold drink
would be fine. Thank you.

676
01:09:18,781 --> 01:09:21,875
Mr. Hammersmith, your office said
I might find you at home.

677
01:09:22,084 --> 01:09:23,745
Hope I'm not troubling you.

678
01:09:24,420 --> 01:09:26,513
Well, that depends, Mr?

679
01:09:26,722 --> 01:09:30,749
Paul Edgecomb. I'm E Block supervisor
up on Cold Mountain.

680
01:09:31,960 --> 01:09:33,324
The Green Mile.

681
01:09:33,528 --> 01:09:36,656
Yeah, I've heard of it.
Lost a few clients your way.

682
01:09:37,432 --> 01:09:40,026
I'd like to ask you about one of them.

683
01:09:41,302 --> 01:09:43,293
- Have a seat.
- Thank you.

684
01:09:48,042 --> 01:09:49,805
Which client?

685
01:09:51,279 --> 01:09:54,077
Now you got my curiosity aroused.

686
01:09:54,282 --> 01:09:55,613
John Coffey.

687
01:09:56,818 --> 01:09:58,217
Coffey.

688
01:09:58,386 --> 01:09:59,614
He causing you problems?

689
01:10:00,088 --> 01:10:03,649
No. Can't say he is. He doesn't like
the dark and cries on occasion...

690
01:10:03,858 --> 01:10:05,723
...but other than that...

691
01:10:05,893 --> 01:10:09,192
He cries, does he?
Well, got a lot to cry about, I'd say.

692
01:10:09,397 --> 01:10:10,955
You know what he did.

693
01:10:11,632 --> 01:10:13,657
I read the court transcript.

694
01:10:14,569 --> 01:10:17,332
- Thank you, missus.
- My pleasure.

695
01:10:18,205 --> 01:10:21,504
Kids! Lunch is about ready.
Y'all come on up.

696
01:10:21,741 --> 01:10:23,038
- Coming, Mama!
- Coming, Mama!

697
01:10:23,243 --> 01:10:26,371
What exactly are you
trying to find out?

698
01:10:26,980 --> 01:10:29,312
I've wondered if he did anything
like that before.

699
01:10:30,784 --> 01:10:32,752
Why? Has he said anything?

700
01:10:32,953 --> 01:10:36,116
No, but a man who does
a thing like that...

701
01:10:36,323 --> 01:10:40,225
...has often developed a taste for it
over time. It occurred to me...

702
01:10:40,427 --> 01:10:44,329
...that it might be easy enough
to follow his back trail. Find out.

703
01:10:45,098 --> 01:10:48,898
A man his size, and colored to boot,
can't be that hard to trace.

704
01:10:49,102 --> 01:10:52,094
You'd think so, but you'd be wrong.

705
01:10:52,305 --> 01:10:54,432
Believe me, we tried.

706
01:10:55,275 --> 01:10:57,470
Like he'd dropped out of the sky.

707
01:10:58,278 --> 01:10:59,711
How can that be?

708
01:10:59,946 --> 01:11:04,143
We're in a depression.
A third of the country's out of work.

709
01:11:04,350 --> 01:11:08,377
People are drifting by the thousands,
looking for jobs, for greener grass.

710
01:11:08,621 --> 01:11:11,749
Even a giant like Coffey
wouldn't get noticed everywhere.

711
01:11:12,525 --> 01:11:14,857
Not until he kills
a couple of little girls.

712
01:11:15,694 --> 01:11:17,286
He is...

713
01:11:17,630 --> 01:11:19,689
...strange, I admit.

714
01:11:20,065 --> 01:11:24,365
But there doesn't seem to be
any real violence in him.

715
01:11:24,803 --> 01:11:27,237
I know violent men, Mr. Hammersmith.

716
01:11:27,473 --> 01:11:30,306
I deal with them day in and day out.

717
01:11:31,110 --> 01:11:33,772
You didn't come to ask me
whether he killed before.

718
01:11:33,979 --> 01:11:36,914
You came to see if I think
he did it at all.

719
01:11:38,317 --> 01:11:40,012
Do you?

720
01:11:41,220 --> 01:11:43,381
One seldom sees a less ambiguous case.

721
01:11:43,589 --> 01:11:45,648
He was found with the victims
in his arms.

722
01:11:45,858 --> 01:11:47,654
And yet you defended him.

723
01:11:48,660 --> 01:11:51,254
Everyone is entitled to a defense.

724
01:11:51,663 --> 01:11:53,290
Kids! Lunch!

725
01:11:53,498 --> 01:11:54,795
Y'all listen to your mama!

726
01:11:59,437 --> 01:12:00,995
I'll tell you something.

727
01:12:02,073 --> 01:12:05,668
And you listen close too, because it
might be something you need to know.

728
01:12:05,877 --> 01:12:07,242
I'm listening.

729
01:12:08,680 --> 01:12:10,614
We had us a dog.

730
01:12:10,782 --> 01:12:12,807
Just a sweet mongrel.

731
01:12:13,017 --> 01:12:14,507
You know the kind.

732
01:12:15,887 --> 01:12:19,323
Well, in many ways,
a good mongrel dog is like a Negro.

733
01:12:20,191 --> 01:12:21,954
You get to know it.

734
01:12:22,160 --> 01:12:26,529
Often, you get to love it.
It is of no particular use...

735
01:12:26,731 --> 01:12:30,258
...but you keep it around
because you think it loves you.

736
01:12:31,768 --> 01:12:35,898
If you're lucky, Mr. Edgecomb, you
never have to find out any different.

737
01:12:36,974 --> 01:12:39,169
My wife and I were not so lucky.

738
01:12:41,144 --> 01:12:42,668
Caleb, come here for a second.

739
01:12:44,081 --> 01:12:45,275
Come here.

740
01:12:46,717 --> 01:12:47,979
Please, son.

741
01:12:49,586 --> 01:12:52,054
He still has the one good eye.

742
01:12:53,423 --> 01:12:55,687
I suppose he's lucky...

743
01:12:55,892 --> 01:12:58,258
...not to be completely blind.

744
01:13:00,964 --> 01:13:04,730
We get down on our knees and thank God
for that much at least.

745
01:13:05,402 --> 01:13:06,801
Right, Caleb?

746
01:13:09,273 --> 01:13:10,570
Okay, go on in now.

747
01:13:14,011 --> 01:13:16,945
That dog attacked my boy
for no reason.

748
01:13:17,546 --> 01:13:19,741
Just got it in his mind one day.

749
01:13:20,516 --> 01:13:21,983
The same with John Coffey.

750
01:13:22,184 --> 01:13:26,416
He was sorry afterwards.
Of that I have no doubt.

751
01:13:27,089 --> 01:13:28,954
But those little girls...

752
01:13:29,158 --> 01:13:31,592
...stayed raped and murdered.

753
01:13:32,261 --> 01:13:34,252
Maybe he'd never done it before.

754
01:13:36,032 --> 01:13:38,193
My dog never bit before.

755
01:13:39,935 --> 01:13:42,665
But I didn't concern myself with that.

756
01:13:43,673 --> 01:13:47,632
I went out with my rifle, grabbed
his collar and blew his brains out.

757
01:13:49,011 --> 01:13:50,171
Is Coffey guilty?

758
01:13:53,115 --> 01:13:54,844
Yes, he is.

759
01:13:55,451 --> 01:13:57,112
Don't you doubt it.

760
01:13:57,486 --> 01:13:59,954
And don't you turn your back on him.

761
01:14:00,790 --> 01:14:04,953
You may get away with it once
or even a hundred times...

762
01:14:05,794 --> 01:14:07,455
...but in the end...

763
01:14:09,464 --> 01:14:10,931
