1511
02:30:14,450 --> 02:30:15,712
Why?

1512
02:30:16,619 --> 02:30:17,881
Why Wild Bill?

1513
02:30:19,221 --> 02:30:23,521
I saw in his heart
when he grabbed my arm.

1514
02:30:24,460 --> 02:30:26,360
I saw what Wild Billy had done.

1515
02:30:26,962 --> 02:30:29,362
Saw it plain as day.

1516
02:30:30,466 --> 02:30:33,333
You can't hide what's in your heart.

1517
02:30:33,636 --> 02:30:34,796
What?

1518
02:30:36,639 --> 02:30:37,799
You saw what?

1519
02:30:41,677 --> 02:30:43,804
Take my hand, boss.

1520
02:30:46,949 --> 02:30:48,712
You see for yourself.

1521
02:30:50,686 --> 02:30:52,244
Paul...

1522
02:30:52,421 --> 02:30:53,479
...no.

1523
02:30:57,525 --> 02:30:58,924
Please.

1524
02:31:07,335 --> 02:31:08,996
No, no.

1525
02:31:10,305 --> 02:31:13,001
- Please.
- I gots to, boss.

1526
02:31:13,174 --> 02:31:15,665
I gots to give you
a little bit of myself.

1527
02:31:17,412 --> 02:31:18,845
A gift.

1528
02:31:20,181 --> 02:31:24,413
A gift of what's inside of me
so you can see for yourself.

1529
02:31:37,632 --> 02:31:39,657
<i>Paul!</i>

1530
02:32:18,372 --> 02:32:20,272
Klaus!

1531
02:32:22,242 --> 02:32:23,800
Suppertime!

1532
02:32:23,977 --> 02:32:25,842
Bring the girls.

1533
02:32:29,315 --> 02:32:32,250
Girls! You heard your mama!

1534
02:32:33,119 --> 02:32:35,849
Yes, Papa! We're coming!

1535
02:32:54,207 --> 02:32:57,938
Come on, Billy.
I worked you enough for one day.

1536
02:32:58,110 --> 02:32:59,839
Come get you some supper.

1537
02:33:02,782 --> 02:33:06,980
<i>God is great, God is good,
and we thank you...</i>

1538
02:33:31,376 --> 02:33:36,109
<i>You love your sister? You make
any noise, you know what happens?</i>

1539
02:33:36,314 --> 02:33:38,407
I'm gonna kill her instead of you.

1540
02:33:38,650 --> 02:33:42,142
You make any noise,
I'm gonna kill her. You understand?

1541
02:33:42,354 --> 02:33:43,981
You understand?

1542
02:34:02,506 --> 02:34:06,499
He killed them with they love,
they love for each other.

1543
02:34:07,745 --> 02:34:10,077
Now you see how it is.

1544
02:34:11,382 --> 02:34:14,283
That's the way it is every day.

1545
02:34:14,518 --> 02:34:18,682
That's the way it is
all over the world.

1546
02:34:28,899 --> 02:34:30,025
Percy.

1547
02:34:30,200 --> 02:34:31,428
Percy Wetmore.

1548
02:34:32,369 --> 02:34:35,736
- Son?
- Percy. Percy Wetmore.

1549
02:34:36,407 --> 02:34:37,704
Son?

1550
02:34:38,375 --> 02:34:41,366
- Son, can you hear me?
- Speak up if you can hear us.

1551
02:34:42,378 --> 02:34:45,438
I think this boy's cheese
slid off his cracker.

1552
02:34:47,216 --> 02:34:50,151
Percy, I got to ask you
a few questions.

1553
02:34:50,386 --> 02:34:53,651
That's right. One minute, he was fine,
and the next, blammo.

1554
02:34:53,890 --> 02:34:56,290
Dirty bastard grabbed him
through the bars.

1555
02:34:56,492 --> 02:34:59,120
Scared the boy so bad, he wet hisself.

1556
02:35:00,063 --> 02:35:02,964
See, we didn't even see it happen.

1557
02:35:06,903 --> 02:35:10,236
I'll cover for you as much as I can...

1558
02:35:10,440 --> 02:35:12,738
...even if it means my job.

1559
02:35:13,409 --> 02:35:15,468
But I have to know...

1560
02:35:15,645 --> 02:35:19,206
...does this have anything to do
with what happened at my house?

1561
02:35:21,751 --> 02:35:23,275
Does it, Paul?

1562
02:35:25,187 --> 02:35:26,449
No.

1563
02:36:53,874 --> 02:36:57,673
Does Hal know?
That Coffey's innocent, I mean.

1564
02:36:58,945 --> 02:37:00,674
Well, can he help?

1565
02:37:01,247 --> 02:37:04,045
Does he have the influence to do
something about this?

1566
02:37:04,250 --> 02:37:07,014
- Stop the execution?
- No.

1567
02:37:10,190 --> 02:37:11,680
Then don't tell him.

1568
02:37:12,358 --> 02:37:14,622
If it can't help, don't tell him.

1569
02:37:14,961 --> 02:37:16,223
Ever.

1570
02:37:18,565 --> 02:37:20,032
I won't.

1571
02:37:31,744 --> 02:37:34,110
There's no way out of this for you,
is there?

1572
02:37:35,582 --> 02:37:36,947
No.

1573
02:37:37,984 --> 02:37:40,543
And I've been thinking about it,
believe me.

1574
02:37:40,752 --> 02:37:45,416
I've been running it through my head
any number of ways. No.

1575
02:37:46,492 --> 02:37:48,619
I'll tell you the truth, honey.

1576
02:37:50,162 --> 02:37:54,997
I've done some things in my life
that I am not proud of...

1577
02:37:55,567 --> 02:38:00,436
...but this is the first time
I've ever felt real danger of hell.

1578
02:38:01,440 --> 02:38:02,805
Hell?

1579
02:38:08,680 --> 02:38:10,307
Talk to him.

1580
02:38:11,483 --> 02:38:13,314
Talk to John.

1581
02:38:15,087 --> 02:38:17,112
Find out what he wants.

1582
02:38:34,038 --> 02:38:35,266
Hello, boss.

1583
02:38:36,274 --> 02:38:37,605
Hello, John.

1584
02:38:39,043 --> 02:38:41,910
I guess you know
we're coming down to it now.

1585
02:38:42,213 --> 02:38:43,942
Another couple of days.

1586
02:38:57,493 --> 02:39:00,291
Is there anything special
you wanna eat that night?

1587
02:39:00,696 --> 02:39:02,994
We can rustle you up most anything.

1588
02:39:13,308 --> 02:39:17,972
Meat loaf be nice.
Mashed taters, gravy.

1589
02:39:18,246 --> 02:39:19,645
Okra.

1590
02:39:20,749 --> 02:39:23,582
Maybe some of that fine corn bread
your missus make...

1591
02:39:24,419 --> 02:39:26,478
...if she don't mind.

1592
02:39:28,790 --> 02:39:30,189
Now...

1593
02:39:30,725 --> 02:39:35,628
...what about a preacher?
Someone to say a little prayer with.

1594
02:39:35,830 --> 02:39:37,991
Don't want no preacher.

1595
02:39:39,034 --> 02:39:41,559
You can say a prayer, if you like.

1596
02:39:42,203 --> 02:39:43,500
Me?

1597
02:39:46,341 --> 02:39:49,174
Suppose I could, if it came to that.

1598
02:39:53,281 --> 02:39:54,804
John...

1599
02:39:57,384 --> 02:40:00,182
I have to ask you something
very important now.

1600
02:40:01,855 --> 02:40:04,050
I know what you gonna say.

1601
02:40:04,525 --> 02:40:06,015
You don't have to say it.

1602
02:40:06,360 --> 02:40:09,693
No, I do. I do. I have to say it.

1603
02:40:10,731 --> 02:40:12,164
John...

1604
02:40:13,634 --> 02:40:15,966
...tell me what you want me to do.

1605
02:40:16,870 --> 02:40:18,861
You want me to take you out of here?

1606
02:40:20,107 --> 02:40:24,100
Just let you run away?
See how far you could get?

1607
02:40:25,579 --> 02:40:28,275
Why would you do such a foolish thing?

1608
02:40:30,284 --> 02:40:32,878
On the day of my judgment...

1609
02:40:33,220 --> 02:40:35,415
...when I stand before God...

1610
02:40:35,623 --> 02:40:39,456
...and he asks me why did I...

1611
02:40:39,659 --> 02:40:42,287
Did I kill one of his true...

1612
02:40:43,162 --> 02:40:44,720
...miracles...

1613
02:40:45,898 --> 02:40:48,059
...what am I going to say?

1614
02:40:49,002 --> 02:40:50,731
That it was my job?

1615
02:40:52,905 --> 02:40:54,896
It's my job.

1616
02:40:55,208 --> 02:40:59,838
You tell God the Father
it was a kindness you done.

1617
02:41:02,982 --> 02:41:05,576
I know you're hurting and worrying.

1618
02:41:06,252 --> 02:41:09,915
I can feel it on you.
But you ought to quit on it now.

1619
02:41:11,090 --> 02:41:14,082
I want it to be over and done with.

1620
02:41:14,761 --> 02:41:16,251
I do.

1621
02:41:20,700 --> 02:41:22,691
I'm tired, boss.

1622
02:41:24,102 --> 02:41:28,471
Tired of being on the road,
lonely as a sparrow in the rain.

1623
02:41:29,675 --> 02:41:32,439
I'm tired of never having me
a buddy to be with...

1624
02:41:33,011 --> 02:41:37,607
...to tell me where we's going to,
coming from, or why.

1625
02:41:38,450 --> 02:41:42,682
Mostly, I'm tired of people
being ugly to each other.

1626
02:41:43,789 --> 02:41:47,748
I'm tired of all the pain
I feel and hear in the world...

1627
02:41:47,959 --> 02:41:49,620
...every day.

1628
02:41:49,995 --> 02:41:51,963
There's too much of it.

1629
02:41:52,297 --> 02:41:56,131
It's like pieces of glass
in my head...

1630
02:41:56,334 --> 02:41:58,632
...all the time.

1631
02:42:00,138 --> 02:42:02,197
Can you understand?

1632
02:42:05,143 --> 02:42:08,112
Yes, John, I think I can.

1633
02:42:10,481 --> 02:42:13,882
Well, there must be something
we can do for you, John.

1634
02:42:16,053 --> 02:42:18,078
There must be something that you want.

1635
02:42:27,498 --> 02:42:31,992
I ain't never seen me a flicker show.

1636
02:42:32,503 --> 02:42:34,630
<i>Neaven</i>

1637
02:42:34,839 --> 02:42:37,000
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

1638
02:42:37,908 --> 02:42:43,505
<i>And my heart beats so
That I can hardly speak</i>

1639
02:42:44,582 --> 02:42:50,543
<i>And I seem to find
The happiness I seek</i>

1640
02:42:51,021 --> 02:42:56,890
<i>When we're out together
Dancing cheek to cheek</i>

1641
02:43:57,920 --> 02:44:00,354
Why, they's angels.

1642
02:44:01,256 --> 02:44:03,918
Angels, just like up in heaven.

1643
02:45:04,585 --> 02:45:06,576
I'll be all right, fellas.

1644
02:45:07,988 --> 02:45:10,252
This here's the hard part.

1645
02:45:11,558 --> 02:45:13,082
I'll be all right in a while.

1646
02:45:14,160 --> 02:45:18,756
John, I should have this just for now.

1647
02:45:22,769 --> 02:45:25,203
I'll give it back after.

1648
02:45:28,341 --> 02:45:32,869
You know, I fell asleep this afternoon
and had me a dream.

1649
02:45:34,080 --> 02:45:36,173
I dreamed about Del's mouse.

1650
02:45:37,350 --> 02:45:38,578
Did you, John?

1651
02:45:39,352 --> 02:45:43,755
I dreamed Mr. Jingles got down to
that place Boss Howell talked about.

1652
02:45:43,957 --> 02:45:46,255
That Mouseville place.

1653
02:45:46,526 --> 02:45:48,858
I dreamed there's kids.

1654
02:45:49,429 --> 02:45:52,864
And how they laughed
at his tricks. My!

1655
02:45:55,367 --> 02:45:59,167
I dreamed that those two little
blond-headed girls was there.

1656
02:45:59,371 --> 02:46:01,236
They's laughing too.

1657
02:46:01,440 --> 02:46:04,375
I put my arms around them
and set them on my knees.

1658
02:46:04,576 --> 02:46:08,637
And they was no blood coming out
of they hair, and they's just fine.

1659
02:46:08,881 --> 02:46:12,214
We all watched Mr. Jingles
roll that spool.

1660
02:46:13,719 --> 02:46:17,155
How we did laugh.
Fit to bust, we was!

1661
02:46:32,938 --> 02:46:34,735
John.

1662
02:46:35,407 --> 02:46:40,400
They's lots of folks here
that hate me. Lots!

1663
02:46:41,412 --> 02:46:43,471
I can feel it.

1664
02:46:43,681 --> 02:46:45,410
It's like bees stinging me.

1665
02:46:45,750 --> 02:46:48,116
Well, feel how we feel, then.

1666
02:46:49,420 --> 02:46:50,648
We don't hate you.

1667
02:46:52,023 --> 02:46:53,581
Can you feel that?

1668
02:46:55,827 --> 02:46:57,988
Kill him twice, you boys!

1669
02:46:58,763 --> 02:47:02,756
You go on and kill that raping
baby killer twice!

1670
02:47:02,967 --> 02:47:04,798
That'd be fine!

1671
02:47:21,486 --> 02:47:23,953
Wipe your face before
you stand up, Dean.

1672
02:47:24,154 --> 02:47:25,451
Yes, sir.

1673
02:47:37,734 --> 02:47:38,792
Roll on one.

1674
02:47:46,810 --> 02:47:50,337
Does it hurt yet? I hope it does.

1675
02:47:51,148 --> 02:47:53,412
I hope it hurts like hell.

1676
02:47:55,352 --> 02:47:59,413
John Coffey, you've been condemned to die
in the electric chair by a jury of your peers.

1677
02:47:59,656 --> 02:48:03,217
Sentence imposed by a judge
in good standing in this state.

1678
02:48:03,527 --> 02:48:06,758
Do you have anything to say
before sentence is carried out?

1679
02:48:08,497 --> 02:48:11,022
I'm sorry for what I am.

1680
02:48:23,045 --> 02:48:24,774
Please, boss...

1681
02:48:26,182 --> 02:48:28,878
...don't put that thing over my face.

1682
02:48:30,086 --> 02:48:32,418
Don't put me in the dark.

1683
02:48:33,189 --> 02:48:35,521
I's afraid of the dark.

1684
02:48:45,201 --> 02:48:46,862
All right, John.

1685
02:49:07,055 --> 02:49:10,081
<i>Neaven, I'm in heaven</i>

1686
02:49:10,291 --> 02:49:13,124
<i>Neaven, heaven</i>

1687
02:49:13,328 --> 02:49:15,159
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

1688
02:49:15,730 --> 02:49:18,324
<i>Neaven, heaven</i>

1689
02:49:18,566 --> 02:49:20,261
<i>I'm in heaven</i>

1690
02:49:41,188 --> 02:49:42,780
John Coffey...

1691
02:49:43,824 --> 02:49:46,952
...electricity shall pass through
your body until you are dead...

1692
02:49:47,161 --> 02:49:49,322
...in accordance with state law.

1693
02:49:51,698 --> 02:49:55,429
May God have mercy on your soul.

1694
02:50:29,769 --> 02:50:30,963
Paul.

1695
02:50:34,140 --> 02:50:36,074
You have to say it.

1696
02:50:37,743 --> 02:50:40,041
You have to give the order.

1697
02:50:58,064 --> 02:51:00,362
<i>Ne killed them with they love.</i>

1698
02:51:00,566 --> 02:51:05,401
<i>That's how it is every day
all over the world.</i>

1699
02:51:19,184 --> 02:51:20,651
Roll on two.

1700
02:53:05,288 --> 02:53:08,655
<i>It was the last execution
I ever took part in.</i>

1701
02:53:08,958 --> 02:53:12,689
I just couldn't do it anymore
after that. Brutal either.

1702
02:53:13,863 --> 02:53:18,562
We both transferred out,
took jobs with Boys' Correctional.

1703
02:53:18,801 --> 02:53:20,563
It was all right.

1704
02:53:21,203 --> 02:53:24,138
"Catch them young" became my motto.

1705
02:53:27,376 --> 02:53:28,502
You don't believe me.

1706
02:53:29,378 --> 02:53:31,903
I don't imagine you'd lie to me, Paul.

1707
02:53:32,714 --> 02:53:34,875
- It's just that...
- It's quite a story.

1708
02:53:35,083 --> 02:53:37,313
It's quite a story.

1709
02:53:37,719 --> 02:53:40,085
One thing I don't understand.

1710
02:53:40,322 --> 02:53:42,085
You said you and Jan...

1711
02:53:42,324 --> 02:53:45,885
...had a grown son in 1935.

1712
02:53:46,161 --> 02:53:47,651
Is that right?

1713
02:53:48,029 --> 02:53:49,997
The math doesn't work, does it?

1714
02:53:55,504 --> 02:53:58,268
Do you feel up to taking a walk?

1715
02:54:18,993 --> 02:54:20,358
Watch your step.

1716
02:54:20,861 --> 02:54:23,193
Now let your eyes adjust.

1717
02:54:34,942 --> 02:54:36,068
There.

1718
02:54:38,712 --> 02:54:41,613
Hey. Wake up, old fella.

1719
02:54:41,882 --> 02:54:43,144
Wake up.

1720
02:54:46,720 --> 02:54:50,587
Paul, it isn't. It can't be.

1721
02:54:54,794 --> 02:54:56,125
Come over here, boy.

1722
02:54:56,629 --> 02:54:58,995
Come on over here and see this lady.

1723
02:55:01,901 --> 02:55:04,927
That can't be Mr. Jingles.

1724
02:55:27,594 --> 02:55:30,188
Go on, you can do it.

1725
02:55:37,269 --> 02:55:41,763
This isn't exactly the Mouseville
we had in mind, is it?

1726
02:55:42,541 --> 02:55:46,500
But we make do. Don't we, old fella?

1727
02:55:52,951 --> 02:55:56,614
I think Mr. Jingles
happened by accident.

1728
02:55:57,055 --> 02:56:01,924
I think when we electrocuted Del,
and it all went so badly...

1729
02:56:02,127 --> 02:56:04,527
...well, John could feel that,
you know.

1730
02:56:04,730 --> 02:56:08,131
And I think a part of...

1731
02:56:08,367 --> 02:56:11,131
...whatever magic was inside of him...

1732
02:56:11,303 --> 02:56:14,636
...just leapt into my tiny friend here.

1733
02:56:15,807 --> 02:56:17,798
As for me...

1734
02:56:18,977 --> 02:56:21,536
...John had to give me
a part of himself...

1735
02:56:21,812 --> 02:56:23,973
...a gift, the way he saw it...

1736
02:56:24,315 --> 02:56:27,751
...so that I could see for myself
what Wild Bill had done.

1737
02:56:30,154 --> 02:56:32,384
When John did that...

1738
02:56:33,824 --> 02:56:36,156
...when he took my hand...

1739
02:56:37,161 --> 02:56:41,063
...a part of the power
that worked through him...

1740
02:56:41,999 --> 02:56:43,864
...spilled into me.

1741
02:56:44,235 --> 02:56:46,066
He what?

1742
02:56:46,504 --> 02:56:50,031
He infected you with life?

1743
02:56:51,609 --> 02:56:53,941
It's as good a word as any.

1744
02:56:55,446 --> 02:56:58,347
He infected us both,
didn't he, Mr. Jingles?

1745
02:56:58,549 --> 02:57:00,016
With life.

1746
02:57:04,088 --> 02:57:07,181
I'm 108 years old, Elaine.

1747
02:57:07,424 --> 02:57:11,793
I was 44 the year that John Coffey
walked the Green Mile.

1748
02:57:14,698 --> 02:57:18,464
You mustn't blame John.
He couldn't help what happened.

1749
02:57:18,702 --> 02:57:23,264
He was just a force of nature.

1750
02:57:23,707 --> 02:57:27,905
Oh, I've lived to see
some amazing things, Ellie.

1751
02:57:28,945 --> 02:57:31,914
Another century come to pass.

1752
02:57:32,148 --> 02:57:34,013
But I've...

1753
02:57:34,651 --> 02:57:39,111
I've had to see my friends and
loved ones die off through the years.

1754
02:57:39,489 --> 02:57:41,548
Hal and Melinda...

1755
02:57:41,992 --> 02:57:43,425
...Brutus Howell...

1756
02:57:43,627 --> 02:57:46,289
...my wife, my boy.

1757
02:57:49,232 --> 02:57:51,096
And you, Elaine.

1758
02:57:52,101 --> 02:57:53,898
You'll die too.

1759
02:57:55,404 --> 02:57:59,807
And my curse is knowing
that I'll be there to see it.

1760
02:58:01,243 --> 02:58:03,677
It's my atonement, you see.

1761
02:58:04,246 --> 02:58:05,975
It's my punishment...

1762
02:58:06,181 --> 02:58:08,809
...for letting John Coffey
ride the lightning.

1763
02:58:10,519 --> 02:58:13,283
<i>For killing a miracle of God.</i>

1764
02:58:14,823 --> 02:58:17,587
<i>Almighty, everlasting God...</i>

1765
02:58:17,893 --> 02:58:20,293
...the source of all being and life...

1766
02:58:20,496 --> 02:58:24,830
<i>You'll be gone like all the others.
I'll have to stay.</i>

1767
02:58:26,835 --> 02:58:31,033
<i>Oh, I'll die eventually.
Of that I'm sure.</i>

1768
02:58:31,774 --> 02:58:35,766
<i>I have no illusions of immortality.</i>

1769
02:58:36,144 --> 02:58:38,738
<i>But I will have wished for death...</i>

1770
02:58:38,913 --> 02:58:41,541
<i>... long before death finds me.</i>

1771
02:58:42,650 --> 02:58:46,484
<i>In truth, I wish for it already.</i>

1772
02:58:58,566 --> 02:59:00,557
Mr. Jingles?

1773
02:59:09,544 --> 02:59:11,705
Where you been?

1774
02:59:12,046 --> 02:59:15,413
Been worried about you, boy.
You hungry?

1775
02:59:16,250 --> 02:59:18,684
Let's go see if we can't find you
something to eat.

1776
02:59:19,820 --> 02:59:23,551
A few crumbs anyway.
I know you'd like that.

1777
02:59:24,991 --> 02:59:26,322
Look at you.

1778
02:59:28,028 --> 02:59:31,930
<i>I lie in bed most nights
thinking about it.</i>

1779
02:59:32,132 --> 02:59:34,157
<i>And I wait.</i>

1780
02:59:34,868 --> 02:59:37,803
<i>I think about all the people
I've loved...</i>

1781
02:59:38,004 --> 02:59:40,165
<i>... now long gone.</i>

1782
02:59:40,741 --> 02:59:43,335
<i>I think about my beautiful Jan...</i>

1783
02:59:43,543 --> 02:59:46,569
<i>... how I lost her so many years ago.</i>

1784
02:59:47,948 --> 02:59:52,578
<i>And I think about all of us walking
our own Green Mile...</i>

1785
02:59:52,786 --> 02:59:55,448
<i>... each in our own time.</i>

1786
02:59:56,523 --> 02:59:59,720
<i>But one thought
more than any other...</i>

1787
02:59:59,926 --> 03:00:02,554
<i>... keeps me awake most nights:</i>

1788
03:00:03,729 --> 03:00:07,688
<i>If he could make a mouse
live so long...</i>

1789
03:00:08,033 --> 03:00:11,264
<i>... how much longer do I have?</i>

1790
03:00:14,573 --> 03:00:17,337
<i>We each owe a death.</i>

1791
03:00:17,543 --> 03:00:20,034
<i>There are no exceptions.</i>

1792
03:00:20,813 --> 03:00:22,804
<i>But, oh, God...</i>

1793
03:00:23,716 --> 03:00:25,513
<i>... sometimes...</i>

1794
03:00:26,118 --> 03:00:29,713
<i>... the Green Mile seems so long.</i>

